        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Exodus 20</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="line-13-2" n="13" prev="ADub.III.73.002.019.trl.xml#line-13-1" />
                        <l n="1">And God spoke
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            all these words, saying,</l><l n="2">‘I am
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            the Lord your God, who has brought you out from land of Egypt,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            from the reign of slaves.</l><l n="3">You shall have no other gods
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            before my eternity.</l><l n="4">You shall not make to yourself any
                            carved idol
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            of any image that you would see in the skies above or that is in the earth
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            beneath, or that is in the water under the earth.</l><l n="5">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            You shall not bow down to them, nor serve them, because I am
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            the Lord your God, God that is jealous, remembering the iniquity of the fathers
                            <milestone unit="page" n="119r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            on the wicked children to the third generation and fourth
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            generation for my enemies.</l><l n="6">But I am he who shows
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            mercy to thousands of generations that love reading my Law, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            that keep my commandments.</l><l n="7">You shall not swear to the name
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            of the Lord your God falsely, because the Lord will not make him guiltless
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            that who would swear to his name in vain.</l><l n="8">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            Remember the Sabbath day, to keep it holy.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="9">Six days shall you labour and do all your work,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="10">And the seventh day is the Sabbath for the praise of the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            your God. You shall not do any work on it, you and your son and your
                            daughter, your manservant and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            your maidservant, and your livestock and your stranger that is within
                            your cities.</l><l n="11">Because
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            in six days the Lord created the skies,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            and the earth, the sea, and all that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            is in them, and he rested on the seventh day. On account of this
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            the Lord blessed the Sabbath day and sanctified it.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="12">Honour your father and your mother, so that your
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            days may be prolonged on the land that the Lord your God is giving to
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            you.</l>
                        <lg n="13">
                            <l n="13">You shall not murder.</l>
                            <l n="14">You shall not commit
                                <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                                adultery.</l>
                            <l n="15">You shall not steal.</l>
                            <l n="16">You shall not
                                <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                                testify against your fellow to be a false witness.</l>
                        </lg>
                        <l n="17">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            You shall not covet your fellow’s house, you shall not covet your
                            fellow’s wife
                            <milestone unit="page" n="119v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            or his manservant or his maidservant or his bull or his donkey
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            or anything that your fellow has.’</l><l n="18">And all the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            people saw the thunders and the torches
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            and the sound of the trumpet and the mountain smoking.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            And the people saw, and they worried and stood far off.</l><l n="19">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            And they said to Moses, ‘Speak you with us, and we will listen,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            but let not God speak with us, lest we die.’</l><l n="20">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            And Moses said to the people, ‘Do not fear, because
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            God’s divine Presence has come to accustom you to the fear of him,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            and that the fear of him may be before your faces,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            so that you may not sin.’</l><l n="21">And the people stood
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            far off, and Moses drew near to the mist where
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            God’s divine Presence was.</l><l n="22">And the Lord said to Moses,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            ‘Thus shall you say to the children of Israel, “You have seen that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            I have talked with you from the skies <seg type="commented" corresp="#seg001"
                             />and you have not seen any
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            figure<anchor type="commented" xml:id="seg001" /><ref target="#fn1"
                                type="noteAnchor" />.</l><l n="23">Therefore you shall not make
                            before me
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            idols of silver, and you shall not make idols of gold for
                            yourselves.</l><l n="24">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            You shall make an altar of earth before me, and you shall sacrifice on it
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            your burnt offerings and your peace offerings, your sheep
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            and your cattle. In every place where you would make my name remembered,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            I will come to you through my providence, and I will bless
                            <milestone unit="page" n="120r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            you.</l><l n="25">And if you make before me an altar of stone,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            you shall not build it of hewn stone. Because if you elevate your sword
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            over it, you will disrespect it.</l><l n="26">And you shall go up
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            by steps to it, that your nakedness should not appear
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            on it.”’</l></ab>
                </div>
